grid = pygmt.datasets.load_earth_relief(
    resolution="02m", region=[161, 185, -50, -30], registration="gridline"
)
grid

grdblend [NOTICE]: Remote data courtesy of GMT data server oceania [http://oceania.generic-mapping-tools.org]
grdblend [NOTICE]: SRTM15 Earth Relief at 02x02 arc minutes reduced by Gaussian Cartesian filtering (3.8 km fullwidth) [Tozer et al., 2019].
grdblend [NOTICE]:   -> Download 60x60 degree grid tile (earth_relief_02m_g): S90W180

f, ax = plt.subplots(subplot_kw=dict(projection=ccrs.PlateCarree(central_longitude=180)))
grid.plot(ax=ax, transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), levels=50)
ax.coastlines('10m', lw=0.5)
